          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrots</strong> into batons</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>shallots</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>halved shallots</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or 2!) and top with your <strong>duck legs</strong> and <strong>white duck fat</strong> (reserve the duck jelly for later!)</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>to the other side, then put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
