    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pot clean and add your <strong>cornflour</strong> and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and mix until fully combined</p><p>Return the pot to a medium heat with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>red wine paste</strong>, <strong>redcurrant jelly </strong>and the <strong>reserved duck jelly </strong>with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>red wine & duck jus</strong></p>",
